public abstract class ActionImpl<R extends Response,A extends Action,C extends BaseRPCServiceCache>
extends java.lang.Object

This class must be implemented in order to perform an action and return a response via the RPC service. It is called automatically by TestRPCServiceImpl depending on the value of the annotation CalledAnnotation. It sole method must return an instance of the Response class R and it will be send by the TestRPCServiceImpl to the requester. If this application uses a cache, the session is available in this class via the method getHttpSession().

Author:
Florian Gimbert
